&lt;li&gt;delete the Main Camera&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Add controller support&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, we can add an avatar for our player. We will use Oculus’ LocalAvatar prefab to see only our hands. The RemoteAvatar prefab is intended for seeing other visitors’ avatars.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the Project pane, expand Assets &gt; Oculus &gt; Avatar &gt; Content &gt; Prefabs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
